1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,520
When you are finished manipulating your data,

2
00:00:02,520 --> 00:00:04,815
it is time to communicate your results.

3
00:00:04,815 --> 00:00:08,250
In order to do so, we'll need some additional techniques.

4
00:00:08,250 --> 00:00:13,065
Descriptive statistics can provide us with concise and comprehensive insights.

5
00:00:13,065 --> 00:00:18,375
We'll start by using the group-by functionality to aggregate our data in different ways.

6
00:00:18,375 --> 00:00:21,855
Then we'll practice summarizing our data through summation,

7
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:25,665
measures of center, and measures of spread.

8
00:00:25,665 --> 00:00:28,920
Next, we'll spend time learning the functionality within

9
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:32,265
pandas to create quick and robust visualizations.

10
00:00:32,265 --> 00:00:36,105
These include but are not limited to histograms,

11
00:00:36,105 --> 00:00:40,530
scatter plots, box plots,

12
00:00:40,530 --> 00:00:44,575
bar plots, and pie charts.

13
00:00:44,575 --> 00:00:47,690
With those descriptive statistics and visualizations,

14
00:00:47,690 --> 00:00:51,305
we'll start to think about what conclusions we can draw from them.

15
00:00:51,305 --> 00:00:56,060
Conclusions are generally derived by asking questions about the summary statistics,

16
00:00:56,060 --> 00:00:59,905
which are further explored and answered with visualizations.

17
00:00:59,905 --> 00:01:03,125
Finally, we will learn about the ways to change

18
00:01:03,125 --> 00:01:06,125
our visualizations to help build effective conclusions,

19
00:01:06,125 --> 00:01:09,530
including altering visualizations by figure size,

20
00:01:09,530 --> 00:01:14,485
labeling, color, and visualization type.

21
00:01:14,485 --> 00:01:16,640
Visualization is such a fun and

22
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:19,790
exciting area because it brings out the creative spark in you.

23
00:01:19,790 --> 00:01:22,740
Let's dive right in and get started.

